  "title": "RESIDENT ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>CSCE PTE. LTD.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>The resident engineer leads on-site construction supervision to ensure compliance with safety and quality standards, driving project success through effective communication, rigorous quality control, and seamless collaboration with stakeholders.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead on-site supervision of construction activities to enforce compliance with safety regulations and quality standards</li><li>Conduct regular inspections and tests on materials and workmanship to verify adherence to project specifications and quality requirements</li><li>Facilitate clear and timely communication between clients, contractors, and project teams to align project objectives and resolve issues</li><li>Maintain accurate and comprehensive documentation of daily activities, progress, and inspection reports to support project tracking and evaluation</li><li>Ensure all construction activities comply with applicable legal and regulatory requirements to mitigate risks and uphold standards</li><li>Collaborate with multidisciplinary professionals to integrate project components and achieve cohesive execution</li><li>Apply engineering principles and technical knowledge to assess construction processes and recommend improvements</li><li>Manage multiple tasks effectively by prioritizing responsibilities and meeting project deadlines</li><li>Analyze on-site challenges promptly and develop practical solutions to maintain project momentum</li><li>Communicate complex technical information clearly in both written and verbal formats to diverse stakeholders</li><li>Exercise meticulous attention to detail to identify discrepancies and uphold quality assurance throughout the project lifecycle</li></ul>",
